WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.090 --> 00:00:03.660
We are all experiencing
this massive propulsion

00:00:03.660 --> 00:00:04.860
for the first time in history.

00:00:04.860 --> 00:00:06.480
And I think what's really
exciting for us is we get

00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:09.090
to be at the heart of the legal industry.

00:00:09.090 --> 00:00:11.730
That is actually one of the oldest jobs

00:00:11.730 --> 00:00:14.100
in the world interpreting the law,

00:00:14.100 --> 00:00:16.230
and how we're gonna structure our society.

00:00:16.230 --> 00:00:21.230
And I think that carries with
it a lot of responsibility.

00:00:21.749 --> 00:00:24.499
(tranquil music)

00:00:26.280 --> 00:00:29.370
Legora is the place
where legal work happens,

00:00:29.370 --> 00:00:32.700
whether that's done by
a human or by an agent

00:00:32.700 --> 00:00:34.290
or in collaboration.

00:00:34.290 --> 00:00:37.710
We help legal work move
faster with reviews,

00:00:37.710 --> 00:00:39.300
drafting and research.

00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:41.460
And we bind all of this together

00:00:41.460 --> 00:00:43.875
into a single cohesive workspace.

00:00:43.875 --> 00:00:47.130
(tranquil music continues)

00:00:47.130 --> 00:00:49.530
- Why are Claude models
specifically good for Legora?

00:00:49.530 --> 00:00:52.710
- A lot of the nuance in drafting

00:00:52.710 --> 00:00:56.970
and reviewing is very context specific.

00:00:56.970 --> 00:00:59.640
You wanna match the style
of the existing document,

00:00:59.640 --> 00:01:01.110
you might wanna match the style

00:01:01.110 --> 00:01:02.820
of that lawyer in particular.

00:01:02.820 --> 00:01:05.670
And there we found the Claude
models, especially Opus,

00:01:05.670 --> 00:01:08.910
extraordinarily good at
the sort of fine drafting.

00:01:08.910 --> 00:01:11.460
This is profoundly
changing the legal industry

00:01:11.460 --> 00:01:13.980
because no technology before

00:01:13.980 --> 00:01:17.430
has ever been able to work
with language and reasoning

00:01:17.430 --> 00:01:18.933
like large language models.

00:01:20.310 --> 00:01:23.910
The very cool thing for us
is that with each new model,

00:01:23.910 --> 00:01:26.101
new capabilities are unlocked.

00:01:26.101 --> 00:01:28.768
(lively music)

00:01:30.630 --> 00:01:33.240
What's happening right
now is every third month

00:01:33.240 --> 00:01:35.100
you guys come up with something new,

00:01:35.100 --> 00:01:36.780
and it's very exciting,

00:01:36.780 --> 00:01:39.480
and it sort of raises
the tide, if you will.

00:01:39.480 --> 00:01:42.660
And so we're thinking a lot
about how do we build the boats

00:01:42.660 --> 00:01:44.580
on top of that rising tide

00:01:44.580 --> 00:01:48.480
so thatour system gets better
with every new model release.

00:01:48.480 --> 00:01:51.540
And we certainly saw this
when we started embedding more

00:01:51.540 --> 00:01:54.180
and more of the Anthropic
models into Legora.

00:01:54.180 --> 00:01:58.320
This exchange of ideas, what's
working, what's not working,

00:01:58.320 --> 00:02:01.592
where do we need to push further,
that has been incredible.

00:02:01.592 --> 00:02:05.009
(lively music continues)

00:02:05.850 --> 00:02:07.440
I think when I look at differentiation,

00:02:07.440 --> 00:02:09.600
it's about how do we make sure

00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:12.240
that Legora has the highest velocity out

00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:14.070
of any company in the industry,

00:02:14.070 --> 00:02:17.790
so that if you place a
bet on us and your firm

00:02:17.790 --> 00:02:20.100
or legal team goes all in on Legora,

00:02:20.100 --> 00:02:21.753
we're going all in on you.

00:02:22.920 --> 00:02:26.640
You're picking a software
partner, an AI partner.

00:02:26.640 --> 00:02:30.360
The people who can harness the power

00:02:30.360 --> 00:02:34.050
of AI will do so much more in the future.

00:02:34.050 --> 00:02:35.970
And the sort of constraints

00:02:35.970 --> 00:02:38.821
about how much you can do
is starting to disappear.

00:02:38.821 --> 00:02:41.321
(happy music)

